---
import LegalLayout from '@/layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  locale="en"
  title="Cookie Policy"
  effectiveDate="Effective May 17, 2026"
  tldr={[
    'We use strictly necessary cookies and one analytics tool to improve DailyMood.',
    'Analytics (Google Analytics) only runs after you click "Accept all" on the consent banner.',
    'No advertising cookies. We never sell your data.',
    'You can withdraw consent anytime by clearing your browser cookies.',
  ]}
>
  <h2>1. Scope of this policy</h2>
  <p>
    This policy covers both <strong>dailymood.me</strong> (the landing site)
    and <strong>my.dailymood.me</strong> (the actual web app). Each domain
    sets its own cookies; the list below covers both.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Strictly necessary cookies</h2>
  <p>
    These are required for the service to function. Under PDPA, they don't
    require consent. If you block them, the site won't work.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Session cookie</strong> (`next-auth.session-token`) —
      keeps you logged in on my.dailymood.me. Managed by NextAuth.js.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>CSRF token</strong> — protects against cross-site request
      forgery attacks.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Stripe</strong> (`m`, `__stripe_mid`) — set when you reach
      Stripe Checkout to prevent fraud. Set directly by Stripe.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>`dm-consent`</strong> — stores your cookie consent choice
      (value is `all` or `necessary`). Lives in your browser's localStorage.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Preference cookies</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>`NEXT_LOCALE` / `dm-lang`</strong> — remembers your language
      choice (Thai or English) so you see the right one on your next visit.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Analytics cookies — consent required</h2>
  <p>
    We use <strong>Google Analytics 4 (GA4)</strong> to understand how
    people use the site (which pages get the most visits, which browsers
    people use, etc.). We don't identify individuals.
  </p>
  <p>Cookies set by GA4:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>`_ga`</strong> — distinguishes unique users. 2-year expiry.</li>
    <li><strong>`_ga_*`</strong> — session state per property.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    These cookies do <strong>not load</strong> until you click "Accept all"
    on the consent banner. If you choose "Only necessary" — or don't
    interact with the banner — Google Analytics is never loaded.
  </p>

  <h2>5. What we don't use</h2>
  <p>To be clear, we do not use:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Advertising cookies (Google Ads, Meta Pixel, TikTok Pixel)</li>
    <li>Session recording tools (Hotjar, FullStory)</li>
    <li>Third-party chat widgets (Intercom, Crisp)</li>
    <li>Embedded YouTube / Twitter / Instagram on our pages</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Third-party data processors</h2>
  <p>
    The providers below process data server-side — they don't set cookies
    in your browser, but PDPA requires us to disclose them:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Google</strong> — OAuth (login) and AI models for AI features.</li>
    <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — payment processing for Pro.</li>
    <li><strong>Resend</strong> — transactional email (verification, password reset).</li>
    <li><strong>Cloudflare R2</strong> — image and avatar storage.</li>
    <li><strong>Cloud hosting provider</strong> — runs our app and database.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    See our <a href="/en/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for more detail.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Managing and withdrawing consent</h2>
  <p>You can change your mind anytime:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Clear your browser's localStorage and cookies</strong> to make
      the consent banner appear again (Chrome: Settings → Privacy → Cookies).
    </li>
    <li>Block all cookies via your browser settings.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>Note:</strong> If you block strictly-necessary cookies, you
    won't be able to log in and core DailyMood features won't work.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Contact our DPO</h2>
  <p>
    For questions about cookies or data protection, contact our Data
    Protection Officer at
    <a href="mailto:hello@dailymood.me">hello@dailymood.me</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
